The withContext HOC has much more flexibility that you can find in the doc page.
Using DataHandlers for shared state
DataHandlers provide a way to wire up TAO handlers into your React Component tree that capture
data and make it available to child and decendant components down the hierarchy.
The Provider sets up the initial data context as a map, and DataHandlers will modify that map
when they react to their configured AppCons.
Let's say we want to classify Spaces using a type field so we need a list of types as a
lookup.  We'll modify our SpaceContainer to capture this list and make it available to it's
children.
src/components/space/index.js with types
